WEBVTT

00:02.419 --> 00:09.257
SCIENTIST: Ladies and gentlemen,
a cybeltronic, self-sustaining heart.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.725
LAB TECH:
Start preparations for transplant.

00:20.895 --> 00:23.022
The subject is prepped for the upgrade.

00:23.982 --> 00:27.099
Okay, my blurry, butt-kicking friend,
you were right.

00:27.569 --> 00:30.276
Tess of the uber-villains is up to no good.

00:30.447 --> 00:33.780
She is hoarding more meteor rock
than there is in all of Smallville.

00:34.659 --> 00:38.197
Something tells me
the reason is behind that curtain.

00:47.505 --> 00:49.120
Hank, huh?

00:50.091 --> 00:51.706
I don't think so.

00:52.469 --> 00:54.801
Tell that to the bean counters in HR.

00:54.971 --> 00:58.054
They didn't wanna chip in
to buy extra letters to spell Henrietta.

00:58.224 --> 00:59.725
SCIENTIST:
How did she get in here?

00:59.893 --> 01:02.805
Inform the boss
the upgrade has been compromised.

01:04.230 --> 01:05.561
Get rid of her.

01:06.691 --> 01:07.897
[LOIS GRUNTING]

01:08.068 --> 01:10.855
Get off of me.

01:11.988 --> 01:14.650
Oh, my God. He's gone. He's gone.

01:14.824 --> 01:16.485
Lockdown. Now.

01:16.659 --> 01:17.865
[ALARM BLARING]

01:18.036 --> 01:21.153
I need Sector 3 and 4 locked down
immediately. You, come with me.

01:21.831 --> 01:22.991
[GUARD GRUNTS]

01:23.166 --> 01:25.828
COMPUTER [OVER SPEAKERS]:
Biohazard. Lockdown.

01:28.797 --> 01:31.755
Biohazard. Lockdown.

01:33.843 --> 01:36.334
-Oh, God.
-Lockdown.

03:09.105 --> 03:10.185
Hi.

03:11.900 --> 03:12.935
How'd you get in here?

03:18.323 --> 03:20.609
How did I get in here?

03:22.785 --> 03:24.776
-Well, it must have been some night.
-Yeah.

03:24.954 --> 03:29.118
l was chasing down a red-hot lead,
and then hit a dead end.

03:33.296 --> 03:35.457
Lois, what happened to you?

03:37.300 --> 03:41.634
You know, I was just— I was trying too hard
to open up my The Hangover DVD.

03:42.472 --> 03:46.932
You know, with Dad's Swiss army knife.
He was sure I wouldn't put it to good use.

03:47.769 --> 03:50.010
-Wanna kiss it better, soldier?
-What's going on?

03:50.188 --> 03:51.724
You've been AWOL for over a week.

03:52.232 --> 03:56.521
I know we agreed a little mystery
between us would be good, but I'm worried.

03:57.070 --> 04:00.278
Come on, I think it'd be a good idea
if there was nothing between us.

04:02.033 --> 04:04.649
I think that can be arranged.

04:04.827 --> 04:06.658
-Lois....
-Mm-hm?

04:09.874 --> 04:11.660
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

04:17.215 --> 04:19.752
I'm sorry, Smallville. It's Randall.

04:20.510 --> 04:22.000
Could be the story of the century.

04:22.178 --> 04:24.339
I can't risk a potential
could've, should've, would've.

04:24.514 --> 04:27.506
It's okay. I wouldn't want you
to miss out on something big.

04:32.105 --> 04:33.515
[SIGHS]

04:34.565 --> 04:37.978
Really, really bad timing,
but I won't hold it against you.

04:38.152 --> 04:41.565
RANDALL: Have you found
the information on Mercer I requested?

04:41.864 --> 04:45.322
Yeah, she's running a secret underground
facility at Fourth and Lincoln...

04:45.493 --> 04:47.984
...where she's testing
some red form of meteor rocks.

04:48.162 --> 04:50.619
Score one for obvious column.
I think you knew that...

04:50.790 --> 04:53.782
...since you saved me
from an early obituary, right?

04:54.627 --> 04:56.128
Yeah.

04:56.754 --> 04:58.619
What is she experimenting on?

04:59.549 --> 05:02.712
You know what? If this isn't a matter
of life and death, I really--

05:02.885 --> 05:04.466
l have to go.

05:13.980 --> 05:15.516
Clark?

05:16.399 --> 05:18.014
[RUSTLING]

05:36.044 --> 05:37.909
[MAN GASPING]

05:55.938 --> 05:57.269
LOIS:
John Corben?

05:58.107 --> 06:01.315
I gotta—
I gotta hand it to you, bright eyes.

06:01.486 --> 06:04.398
You sure have a way of ﬁnding trouble.

06:04.572 --> 06:06.813
[CHUCKLING]

06:06.991 --> 06:10.904
Said the man who swatted me around like
a tether ball on our last arena challenge.

06:11.079 --> 06:12.615
| just wanted to get you home.

06:12.789 --> 06:15.075
I didn't-- I didn't mean for you to see me.

06:15.541 --> 06:16.951
Wait. Get me home?

06:17.126 --> 06:19.868
When I woke up on the lab table,
they had altered me.

06:20.046 --> 06:23.209
And my mind—
My mind is almost normal.

06:23.466 --> 06:25.127
It is. It is.

06:25.301 --> 06:29.044
Except for this upgrade here.

06:29.222 --> 06:30.462
It's here. Look.

06:30.640 --> 06:32.471
Upgrade?

06:47.281 --> 06:48.316
John.

06:49.992 --> 06:52.199
John, who did this to you?

06:53.329 --> 06:56.492
-Tess?
-Her scientists did.

06:57.125 --> 07:01.710
I heard them saying something
about slamming a chip in the back...

07:01.879 --> 07:04.962
...so they could control
everything that I do.

07:06.717 --> 07:11.962
But then you helped me escape
before they could.

07:12.348 --> 07:13.679
[BEEPING]

07:14.809 --> 07:15.844
[G ROANS]

07:16.394 --> 07:20.103
John? John, what's happening?
John, look at me.

07:23.568 --> 07:30.030
My heart is gonna stop
if I don't ﬁnd a meteor rock and refuel.

07:46.507 --> 07:48.168
Thank you.

07:54.474 --> 07:56.931
CHLOE [OVER PHONE]:
Okay. Vector ten-and-a-half feet north.

07:57.101 --> 07:58.841
Have I sunk Lois' battleship?

07:59.020 --> 08:01.227
Chloe, I can see 50 feet
in every direction.

08:01.397 --> 08:03.558
There's no reason Lois would've been
in this spot...

08:03.733 --> 08:05.564
-...for two hours last night.
-You know...

08:06.068 --> 08:09.811
...not that I wanna wade into the salty
ocean of amour that is Lois and Clark...

08:09.989 --> 08:12.526
...but if you two are playing
Mr. and Mrs. Smith now...

08:12.700 --> 08:15.032
...don't you think
there might be a trust issue?

08:15.203 --> 08:17.239
I'm worried
she's holding something back.

08:17.997 --> 08:20.739
It's different when the control's
on the other foot.

08:20.917 --> 08:22.532
You know, Clark, Lois trusts you.

08:23.252 --> 08:24.503
Now you need to trust her.

08:24.670 --> 08:26.376
-I do.
-Right.

08:26.547 --> 08:29.380
And that's why you had me
LoJack her key chain?

08:30.635 --> 08:32.421
Clark, I just checked the time code.

08:32.595 --> 08:36.929
If we could rocket back a few hours,
you would be standing on Lois' shoulders.

09:15.471 --> 09:17.507
Clark Kent at the keyboard?

09:17.682 --> 09:20.640
Have I been downsized
in the bureaucratic world of superheroes?

09:20.810 --> 09:22.641
| just got tired of waiting for you.

09:22.812 --> 09:26.304
Oh, snap. Someone woke up on
the wrong side of the planet.

09:26.482 --> 09:30.191
More like the wrong side of Lois.
That'll never happen again. Check this out.

09:30.528 --> 09:32.894
What caught your better-than-bionic eye
this time?

09:33.072 --> 09:36.656
It's Tess. It was her underground lab
that Lois was snooping around in.

09:39.412 --> 09:42.904
What's with the thermo-radioactive scan
of North America?

09:43.082 --> 09:45.619
She's storing meteor rock
around the country.

09:45.793 --> 09:47.829
She's gonna pay for it.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.127
Clark, wait.

09:50.298 --> 09:54.007
As much as I would love to have Tess
out of our lives, you can't take her down.

09:54.176 --> 09:56.303
You're connecting the dots
in the wrong order.

09:58.347 --> 10:00.008
These deposits don't belong to Tess.

10:00.182 --> 10:03.345
Tess is the only one who knows
what kryptonite can do to me.

10:03.519 --> 10:06.261
Except for me...

10:08.024 --> 10:09.685
...and Oliver.

10:15.990 --> 10:18.857
You and Oliver betrayed me.

10:20.536 --> 10:22.697
It sounds worse than it actually—

10:22.872 --> 10:25.033
You're stockpiling weapons
that can kill me.

10:25.207 --> 10:26.458
Not you. Kryptonians.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.036
I'm Kryptonian.

10:28.210 --> 10:30.701
-The weapons are just insurance.
-In case what, Chloe?

10:30.880 --> 10:32.211
In case I turned on you?

10:32.381 --> 10:33.541
[CHLOE GRUNTS]

10:34.383 --> 10:38.968
God, I was such a fool to think
that you could ever understand me.

10:39.138 --> 10:40.719
You think you're better than Tess.

10:40.890 --> 10:44.348
At least she didn't pretend
to be on my side all those years.

10:44.518 --> 10:47.976
Clark, why don't you hear my side?
What if, someday, there was ever a war?

10:48.147 --> 10:50.763
There is a war, Chloe, right now.

10:50.983 --> 10:52.564
And you're about to lose it.

11:35.111 --> 11:36.942
[GRUNTING AND GASPING]

11:40.658 --> 11:41.738
[G ROANING]

11:57.508 --> 11:59.123
[YELLS]

13:00.613 --> 13:02.103
[TIRES SCREECHING]

13:11.957 --> 13:13.618
LOIS:
Corben.

13:14.502 --> 13:15.708
John.

13:15.878 --> 13:18.711
CORBEN:
Lois, stay away.

13:19.757 --> 13:22.214
-John?
-Stay back, Lois.

13:27.181 --> 13:28.717
[CORBEN GROANING]

13:29.934 --> 13:31.049
[LOIS CLEARS THROAT]

13:32.353 --> 13:36.016
-Glad to see you're looking so good.
-Thanks.

13:36.941 --> 13:39.398
You look pretty good too.

13:41.028 --> 13:43.610
I meant, you know, strong.

13:43.781 --> 13:47.273
I mean healthy, alive.

13:48.077 --> 13:49.738
CORBEN:
Right.

13:52.248 --> 13:54.239
Maybe we should get out of here...

13:54.416 --> 13:58.079
...before The Blur decides
to light this place up like a Christmas tree.

13:59.380 --> 14:00.586
The Blur did this to you?

14:01.757 --> 14:03.088
I don't know how he found me.

14:05.261 --> 14:06.922
Well, maybe he wasn't here for you.

14:07.096 --> 14:09.428
Maybe he was following
a well-meaning source.

14:09.598 --> 14:13.762
You did kind of go Phantom of the Boiler
Room last time you entered stage right.

14:35.291 --> 14:38.624
TESS: Last time I checked,
this was private property.

14:39.336 --> 14:43.375
Looks like Tess Mercer's skeleton
is ﬁnally crawling out of the closet.

14:44.675 --> 14:48.543
Well, speaking of being hidden in the closet,
how's Oliver doing these days?

14:49.805 --> 14:52.171
Don't worry
your pretty little head about that.

14:52.349 --> 14:55.716
And by "head," I mean the one
that the secret government agency...

14:55.895 --> 14:58.056
...Checkmate is wanting to lop off.

14:58.230 --> 15:01.973
That must really suck
to be on the outs of your own walls.

15:02.276 --> 15:04.232
I'm guessing you'd know.

15:04.695 --> 15:07.607
Since you're not cuddling up
to your own cyber-screens...

15:08.490 --> 15:11.982
...l'm venturing that Clark has ﬁnally
uncovered your kryptonite arsenal.

15:13.537 --> 15:15.994
This is the last place I sent him.

15:21.837 --> 15:23.793
[GENERATOR POWERS UP]

15:28.260 --> 15:31.502
I should have known Clark
took a walk down the ruby-red road.

15:31.680 --> 15:34.672
That explains his lack of edit button.

15:35.017 --> 15:38.305
I thought Clark was only affected
by green meteor.

15:39.355 --> 15:40.970
What's the red do?

15:41.148 --> 15:44.686
Basically it turns him into the bad boy
every girl dreams of...

15:44.944 --> 15:46.104
...in her nightmares.

15:46.487 --> 15:48.694
And why should I care, huh?

15:48.864 --> 15:51.606
Clark's made it clear
he's not my knight in shining armor...

15:51.784 --> 15:54.196
...which is why I made my own
all-purpose bodyguard.

15:55.746 --> 15:58.533
Well, believe it or not, Tess,
this isn't all about you.

15:58.707 --> 16:03.292
Sooner or later, Clark will out himself
and your merry band of Kryptonians.

16:05.714 --> 16:08.797
If the world gets wind of their existence,
there's no turning back.

16:09.259 --> 16:13.218
Right, but you can protect your alien
pet project if you help me ﬁnd Clark.

16:32.616 --> 16:34.322
[WHOOSHING]

16:38.914 --> 16:41.906
The cleaning baptism
that redeems the soul.

16:45.254 --> 16:46.369
Kierkegaard.

16:48.257 --> 16:50.999
You have to enjoy the paradox.

16:51.427 --> 16:54.669
The only thing on their planet
that can harm us is a piece of our own.

16:57.766 --> 16:59.848
You lied about having powers.

17:02.271 --> 17:03.351
How'd you get them?

17:11.655 --> 17:13.316
From you.

17:14.700 --> 17:16.565
From your blood.

17:18.620 --> 17:19.780
When you saved me.

17:21.498 --> 17:22.829
It's contradictory, isn't it?

17:23.000 --> 17:26.083
But then again,
you are the greatest contradiction of all.

17:26.587 --> 17:28.578
Dedicating your life to the greater good...

17:28.756 --> 17:31.589
...and at the same time,
deceiving those you love the most.

17:32.509 --> 17:34.795
I'm the one who's been deceived.

17:35.637 --> 17:38.128
Oh, come, come, Kal-El.

17:38.474 --> 17:43.013
You have become far too calculating
to play the naive farm boy anymore.

17:43.187 --> 17:48.648
Your closest friends fear you
because they will never understand you.

17:48.817 --> 17:50.557
And how could they?

17:58.452 --> 18:00.317
You need me.

18:01.747 --> 18:04.580
Who else in your world
has ever truly been your equal?

18:07.127 --> 18:09.243
I have no equal.

18:09.671 --> 18:11.627
You really can't see it, can you?

18:12.800 --> 18:18.136
A modem-day messiah whose symbol is
worshiped by the mere mortals at his feet.

18:18.305 --> 18:22.264
A God who rips decisions
out of the hands of fate.

18:23.435 --> 18:28.054
Now there is a real threat out there
to both of us.

18:28.482 --> 18:30.438
With your map
of the kryptonite arsenals...

18:30.609 --> 18:33.521
...we can take out any defense they have
against us.

18:33.695 --> 18:34.855
Nothing can stop us.

18:35.823 --> 18:37.939
Now the question is...

18:38.575 --> 18:40.657
...who will you join?

18:45.040 --> 18:47.031
Your friends?

18:48.293 --> 18:49.749
[ZOD SCOFFS]

18:49.920 --> 18:54.789
Your friends, who have stockpiled weapons
around the world to kill you?

18:56.009 --> 18:59.172
Or the one man
who weighs the same decisions...

18:59.346 --> 19:01.883
...struggles with the same dilemmas...

19:03.142 --> 19:05.884
...and who just saved your life?

19:30.586 --> 19:32.918
MAN [OVER PA]:
Bus 187, the Northern Express...

19:33.088 --> 19:34.919
...is now boarding at Gate 6.

19:35.090 --> 19:37.581
All passengers holding tickets
for New York--

19:37.759 --> 19:39.295
CORBEN:
Lois.

19:39.803 --> 19:44.217
I appreciate you trying to help,
but I've got it from here, all right?

19:44.391 --> 19:47.758
You get yourself into enough trouble
without me leading you to more.

19:48.770 --> 19:52.308
I promised I'd get you to the military base
in South Dakota.

19:59.281 --> 20:02.068
So, what are you,
my personal bodyguard?

20:03.827 --> 20:06.113
My dad assured me Dr. Vale
is the best guy around.

20:06.288 --> 20:09.451
So whether you like it or not,
you're stuck with me.

20:09.625 --> 20:12.037
As nice as that sounds...

20:12.211 --> 20:16.045
...I could have Tess Mercer's entire defense
division descending on me any minute.

20:16.215 --> 20:17.625
Exactly.

20:17.799 --> 20:21.462
When you're free and clear and planting
your homestead spike in the badlands...

20:21.637 --> 20:23.252
...then I'll send you the sayonara.

20:32.814 --> 20:34.350
CORBEN:
Here, let me help you with that.

20:34.524 --> 20:36.731
WOMAN:
Oh, that's so kind of you.

20:52.042 --> 20:53.623
John?

20:56.129 --> 20:57.585
Hey.

21:05.514 --> 21:08.005
ZOD: For someone so reticent
about joining forces...

21:08.183 --> 21:11.892
...you've certainly wasted no time
in destroying Chloe's kryptonite stock hold.

21:12.062 --> 21:15.020
I'm sure there's some quote
about betrayal stinging the most...

21:15.190 --> 21:17.021
...when it's from someone you trust.

21:17.192 --> 21:19.558
Your father could have rattled it off.

21:19.736 --> 21:22.944
-You remind me of him.
-Yeah. Well, I'd rather not hear it.

21:24.199 --> 21:26.815
I didn't get the chance to know him
like you did.

21:27.160 --> 21:31.529
Don't get me wrong.
We used to ﬁght until all hours of the night.

21:32.124 --> 21:34.706
So, what, he was stubborn, like me?

21:34.876 --> 21:36.082
Yeah.

21:37.754 --> 21:40.040
But that never meant
that I didn't respect him.

21:41.508 --> 21:44.841
You must have had a friend
that you had a connection with...

21:45.012 --> 21:47.845
...like you were opposite sides
of the same soul.

21:49.057 --> 21:51.173
Yeah. Once. Along time ago.

21:52.060 --> 21:55.928
You no longer have to be worried
about people envying you...

21:59.067 --> 22:02.059
...because you have a family now,
a family who understands.

22:03.280 --> 22:04.736
Good.

22:05.741 --> 22:07.322
Maybe it's time to live a little.

22:16.877 --> 22:18.617
ZOD:
It's quite a view.

22:19.254 --> 22:21.586
CLARK:
Everything seems so clear from up here.

22:22.716 --> 22:25.332
I'm asking myself
why it took me so long to see it.

22:27.304 --> 22:31.092
Sometimes it just takes somebody
to share your perspective.

22:34.227 --> 22:36.092
If only your father could see us.

22:37.981 --> 22:39.096
He can.

22:41.777 --> 22:45.110
How would you like to say hello
to your old friend Jor-El?

22:54.581 --> 22:59.450
But ﬁrst, let's give the people of Seattle
a little surprise.

23:14.518 --> 23:17.225
TESS: Well, my ops found
our soldier of fortune on a bus.

23:18.397 --> 23:21.981
-Any luck with your problem child?
-How often does it snow in Seattle?

23:22.150 --> 23:25.313
Not a great time
for a game of Trivial Pursuit, Chloe.

23:25.821 --> 23:27.152
No. Seriously, Tess.

23:27.322 --> 23:31.611
Seattle just had a ﬂuke snowstorm
with the temperature at 64 degrees.

23:34.913 --> 23:37.245
Oh, I got it. Thank God for blogging.

23:37.416 --> 23:41.329
They saw something vaulting
towards the space needle six minutes ago.

23:55.559 --> 23:58.722
Guess who's coming for dinner
together...

23:59.688 --> 24:01.599
...with powers.

24:05.986 --> 24:08.477
But you already knew that, didn't you?

24:10.866 --> 24:13.357
What I don't know
is why the sudden bromance.

24:13.535 --> 24:14.945
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

24:44.274 --> 24:46.356
Welcome home, brother.

25:08.632 --> 25:12.671
Well, he isn't exactly rolling out the
welcome mat, is he? Nothing's working.

25:13.094 --> 25:14.834
Which ﬁgures.

25:15.263 --> 25:18.300
As soon as I embrace my heritage,
you vanish.

25:18.475 --> 25:22.718
Given what you told me about my role in
the last days of Krypton, I'm not surprised.

25:22.896 --> 25:25.638
Well, he can't blame you
for something you haven't done yet.

25:25.815 --> 25:29.023
It took you almost a year
to warm up to me.

25:29.236 --> 25:33.855
I wouldn't expect my discerning old friend
to give me any more latitude.

25:34.699 --> 25:38.658
It's all right. I've learned everything I need
from this thing anyway.

25:38.828 --> 25:44.118
Well, don't be too quick to dismiss
what Jor-EI has to offer you, Kal-El.

25:44.292 --> 25:47.284
Trust me, I can live
without constant lectures and mind games.

25:47.462 --> 25:51.626
How about the answers
to everything in the universe?

25:53.802 --> 25:54.882
Give me a break.

25:55.762 --> 25:57.047
I was a skeptic too.

25:58.640 --> 26:04.135
On Krypton, our children are raised
to revere the red sun god, Rao.

26:04.312 --> 26:10.729
Unlike your civilizations,
superstition has no place in our beliefs.

26:12.571 --> 26:15.278
Religion is science...

26:15.615 --> 26:19.483
...not some mystical questioning of it.

26:22.581 --> 26:26.199
Your father left our bible,
the Book of Rao, on this Earth.

26:27.002 --> 26:31.496
And what with all of this,
and the knowledge in that book...

26:31.673 --> 26:35.666
...Kal-El, there is no limit
to what we can achieve.

26:50.066 --> 26:52.352
I lost the GPS feed.

26:54.154 --> 26:55.860
Where'd you send him?

26:58.617 --> 27:00.278
On a hunch.

27:03.371 --> 27:05.407
[CLANG]

27:14.716 --> 27:16.377
Tess.

27:16.760 --> 27:19.502
How not surprised am I to see you here.

27:19.679 --> 27:25.390
By the way, this is the least-secret
secret lab I've ever been in. Twice.

27:26.978 --> 27:29.811
I am so sorry to disappoint you, Lois.

27:30.315 --> 27:33.557
I doubt the government is gonna want
their covert defense programs...

27:33.735 --> 27:37.899
...on the front page of the Daily Planet,
so if you could just, shh.

27:38.406 --> 27:40.021
I saw what you did to Corben.

27:40.575 --> 27:43.908
I was on the bus when you sent me
on a tranq trip to Mount Rushmore.

27:44.079 --> 27:46.195
You can't cover this up, Tess.

27:46.373 --> 27:48.204
[LOIS GRUNTING]

27:52.754 --> 27:54.244
CHLOE:
Sorry, Lo.

27:59.552 --> 28:02.840
You take care of her,
and I'll clean the rest of this up...

28:03.014 --> 28:07.132
...to make sure that no one will believe
Lois' trip down the rabbit hole.

28:16.403 --> 28:17.518
How did he get in here?

28:22.283 --> 28:23.409
Chloe.

28:27.163 --> 28:28.573
[GRUNTING]

28:58.153 --> 29:01.145
Well, I sure do like what you've done
with the place.

29:20.175 --> 29:21.631
[ICE CRACKING]

29:43.239 --> 29:44.979
And I thought I got a chilly welcome.

30:29.410 --> 30:33.574
CORBEN:
I don't blame you for frying me.

30:33.748 --> 30:37.991
But someone who cares about you
sent me here to save you.

30:38.837 --> 30:39.997
And I owe you one.

30:41.214 --> 30:43.250
Is this my lucky day to be saved?

30:46.719 --> 30:48.255
Kal-El.

30:49.806 --> 30:52.343
Take it from someone who's been there.

30:53.601 --> 30:56.593
We don't always know
when we need saving.

30:57.772 --> 30:59.273
[CLARK GROANING]

31:35.685 --> 31:39.303
You can thank me another time.

32:10.345 --> 32:11.835
Zod.

32:23.358 --> 32:25.349
God, do you take lessons
on how to do that?

32:25.526 --> 32:29.895
Okay. Isn't the appropriate response,
"Thank God, you're still alive.

32:31.282 --> 32:33.614
Too bad you're wearing clothes
this time"?

32:33.785 --> 32:35.491
Yes, that's it.

32:35.662 --> 32:37.368
The ﬁrst part.

32:37.538 --> 32:39.278
[MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

32:41.709 --> 32:43.825
So how did you get away from Mercer?

32:44.295 --> 32:45.876
Uh....

32:46.422 --> 32:48.128
It involved a secret cave...

32:48.299 --> 32:52.668
...action sequence out of the Ice Capades,
and your best friend.

32:58.768 --> 33:00.679
LOIS:
Maybe this makes up for everything.

33:10.488 --> 33:11.853
Where'd you get that?

33:13.074 --> 33:15.736
Souvenir from my own little adventure.

33:21.124 --> 33:24.992
You know, the ﬁrst time I saw you, I never
thought that you'd end up being my hero.

33:27.046 --> 33:30.163
Of course, I was hoping to escape
with a different heart.

33:31.134 --> 33:32.965
You know, Lois...

33:33.511 --> 33:36.878
...you're the only one
that's been honest...

33:37.682 --> 33:39.388
...and loyal and brave.

33:40.393 --> 33:44.727
Wow, that's a scary-high pedestal
of adjectives you just put me on.

33:44.897 --> 33:49.061
You're the only one
that's given me a chance. I....

33:51.320 --> 33:55.154
I mean,
I can't ever tell anyone else about me.

33:56.117 --> 33:59.905
You're the only chance that l have
of living an honest...

34:00.830 --> 34:02.866
...honest life.

34:05.418 --> 34:09.787
And if I were gonna disappear again...

34:09.964 --> 34:12.706
...I would wanna disappear with you.

34:15.053 --> 34:16.589
Oh.

34:16.763 --> 34:18.219
Me.

34:19.974 --> 34:23.216
John, that means a lot.

34:25.938 --> 34:30.307
But I'm with someone else.
He's a little on the squeaky side...

34:30.485 --> 34:35.149
...so I probably won't pull back the curtain
and reveal our wild and crazy ride...

34:35.865 --> 34:40.985
...but he is it for me.

34:48.127 --> 34:49.628
Okay.

34:54.717 --> 34:56.628
Sorry. I, uh....

35:02.517 --> 35:04.348
You have one of those words for now?

35:04.852 --> 35:06.262
[CH UCKLES]

35:06.896 --> 35:08.306
Um....

35:10.066 --> 35:13.934
Maybe if this were another lifetime.

35:18.116 --> 35:19.447
Yeah.

35:21.160 --> 35:22.946
You know, I really...

35:23.704 --> 35:26.241
...hope that your guy
knows who you really are...

35:26.415 --> 35:29.202
...because you are a real...

35:33.714 --> 35:36.842
...dame, Lois Lane.

36:10.585 --> 36:13.622
You're not that naive, are you?

36:17.133 --> 36:20.921
If Kal-El and I can work together,
why wouldn't I try?

36:21.095 --> 36:24.087
Because he doesn't have
your best interest at heart.

36:24.765 --> 36:28.758
But you and I,
we have a commitment to each other.

36:36.194 --> 36:38.276
You're not backing out on me, are you?

36:38.446 --> 36:43.281
Well, I'm not the one that sent
a modern-day metal Nero to attack you.

36:45.661 --> 36:47.071
No.

36:48.789 --> 36:50.575
Not today.

37:02.762 --> 37:08.257
You can't bet everything we've worked for,
including the safety of your people...

37:08.434 --> 37:11.050
...on someone
who's so quick to switch allegiances.

37:11.646 --> 37:15.138
I don't think you have any idea
of the power that lies within Kal-El.

37:18.277 --> 37:19.892
Well, I hope you're right.

37:22.615 --> 37:25.231
Because you're losing control
of the Kandorians.

37:34.502 --> 37:36.163
I discovered a secret rebellion.

37:48.975 --> 37:52.012
A group of your people
have turned against you...

37:52.186 --> 37:54.643
...and are looking to a new leader.

37:58.442 --> 37:59.477
Clark.

38:12.164 --> 38:13.495
[WHOOSHING]

38:22.633 --> 38:26.467
I didn't think it would be a good idea
to get the handyman to repair this.

38:28.222 --> 38:31.931
If I had an apology on video, it would
have saved me a lot of time this year.

38:34.353 --> 38:38.221
Well, I'd say I did my fair share
of trespassing, as well.

38:38.399 --> 38:42.062
The part where you were amassing
the only weapons that can kill me?

38:42.236 --> 38:44.522
Yeah, that would be the part.

38:47.241 --> 38:50.483
Maybe you were the one seeing things
clearly from the beginning.

38:51.829 --> 38:54.445
There's something I didn't tell you
about the future.

38:54.832 --> 38:58.370
That your kryptonite armory was
the only thing that saved the world.

39:02.089 --> 39:04.296
And me teaming up with Zod...

39:04.467 --> 39:08.301
...tuming my back on you and Oliver,
that wasn't all the Red Kryptonite.

39:09.472 --> 39:11.087
Curious.

39:11.265 --> 39:14.257
I think it was some sort
of wish-fulﬁllment thing for me.

39:15.728 --> 39:19.687
Clark, if you wanted to redecorate
the place, all you had to do was ask.

39:23.694 --> 39:26.936
It's just that seeing you and Lois together,
you're like sisters.

39:27.114 --> 39:31.027
The two of you have an understanding,
a shorthand that I've never known.

39:31.369 --> 39:32.449
We're family.

39:32.995 --> 39:35.532
That's something
I don't have much of anymore.

39:39.126 --> 39:41.082
I mean, Zod and I...

39:41.587 --> 39:44.044
...we've been on different sides.

39:45.633 --> 39:47.794
We were raised in different worlds.

39:50.930 --> 39:55.014
But somehow, through the isolation
and the burdens, losing our home...

39:55.184 --> 39:59.473
...trying to manage in somebody else's, he
understands things about me nobody can.

40:03.484 --> 40:06.476
Chloe, he's the closest thing to a brother
that I may ever know.

40:24.713 --> 40:28.205
Some of our brothers and sisters
have detected.

40:30.511 --> 40:32.297
I'm afraid we've been betrayed.

40:34.098 --> 40:36.214
But we will prevail.

41:24.773 --> 41:27.480
The time has come
to share in your birthright.

42:15.824 --> 42:17.815
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]
